column1: Supplemental table 1a: List of the final protein N-termini. This list is generared by considering (i) only peptides which start within the first 100 amino acids of the respective protein’s sequence and (ii) only the most N-terminal peptide per protein. This leads to the identification of 806 unique and non-redundant protein N-termini, representing >20% of the expected yeast proteome25, with 661 unique protein N-termini quantified between the two samples.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         25 Nagaraj et al., Mol Cell Proteomics 2012, 11, (3), M111 013722.
